<TITLE> Suspected gas blast at former BNP minister's home injures son, wife </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 17 (bdnews24.com)  A suspected gas explosion in the Gulshan home of the late AM Zahiruddin Khan, a former BNP minister, left son Kalim Khan and Kalim's wife injured on Sunday. Md Harun-ur-Rashid, assistant commissioner of police of Gulshan division, told bdnews24.com the explosion took place on the ground floor of the house on Road 5, Gulshan-2, around noon. "Police are primarily suspecting that it might have been a gas explosion," he said. Sheikh Masud Karim, sub-inspector of Gulshan police station, quoting doctors, said the 32-year-old Kalim had suffered burns to "65 percent of his body". "His wife was released after first aid but Kalim is undergoing treatment in Apollo Hospital." An initial investigation indicated the explosion occurred as Kalim was smoking in a bathroom adjacent to his bedroom, said the sub-inspector. He added that the police had not uncovered any suspicious circumstances surrounding the incident. CID bomb experts inspected the building soon after the explosion, Karim said. They did not find any evidence so far that a bomb exploded inside the house or was thrown at the house," he said. bdnews24.
